    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "- `nvim --version`: NVIM 0.2.0-dev\r\n- Vim (version: 7.4 patch 898) behaves differently? no\r\n- Operating system/version: macOS Sierra\r\n- Terminal name/version: Terminal.app\r\n- `$TERM`: xterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nUndoing a change after `undojoin` restores the cursor to the beginning of the buffer.\r\n\r\n### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nThe cursor should be restored to the location of the joined change.\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce using `nvim -u NORC`\r\n\r\nSave the following commands in a file, eg: `reproduce-err.vim`\r\n\r\n```\r\nnormal ggiline one is bull of aaaa\r\nset undolevels=10 \" splits the change into separate undo blocks\r\n\r\nnormal Goline two is full of bbbb\r\nset undolevels=10 \r\n\r\nnormal Goline three is full of cccc        \r\nset undolevels=10\r\n\r\nnormal Goline four is full of aaaa's again\r\nset undolevels=10\r\n\r\nundojoin\r\nkeepjumps %s/aaaa/zzzz/\r\nnormal u\r\n```\r\nSource the file into an empty vim buffer\r\n```\r\nnvim -u NORC +\"so reproduce-err.vim\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nAlso, if it's of any help, StackOverflow (http://stackoverflow.com/questions/31548025) includes a more verbose write up of the issue (with more examples), and some attempts at locating what's causing it.",
    "closed_at": "2023-09-12T09:50:24Z",
    "comment_data": [
